1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,000
Six villagers. Two teams. One goal:
the first crafted iron pickaxe wins.

2
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:12,000
No scripts. Each villager thinks with a local LLM
every 10 seconds — llama3.1:8b, running on one PC.

3
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:18,000
Normal difficulty. Hostile mobs on.
Zero human intervention from the starting gun.

4
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:36,000
The wood age: axes are free, ores are gated.
Every tool is a project, not a wish.

5
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:53,000
RED draws first blood — first coal,
3 minutes 47 into the race.

6
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:20,000
BLUE answers 27 seconds later.
Both teams have fuel. The ladder steepens.

7
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:47,000
BLUE mines first iron — stone pickaxes only;
the tool gate taught them the hard way.

8
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:52,000
RED finds iron a minute later.
Four rungs down, two to go — anyone's race.

9
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:06,000
BLUE crafts a furnace. 9 minutes flat.
The win is one smelt away.

10
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:52,000
FEN OF BLUE: three ingots smelted and the
IRON PICKAXE CRAFTED — one action, race over.

11
00:10:52,000 --> 00:11:00,000
11 minutes, 0.6 seconds. Judged from an
append-only event ledger — not a screenshot.

12
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:08,000
Honest-race assertion: CLEAN. Zero scripted
decisions, zero budget trips, zero deaths.
Every milestone replayable by one curl.
